The paper focuses on analyzing the link structure of individual web sites, which falls under the category of web science and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also touches upon topics related to web architecture and data structures, which could fall under cs.WEB (Web Technologies) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of the web site link structure with other types of networks, which could fall under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity).
